(40, 20, 28, 60, 3, 18, 18, 'give his life a ransom for many', 'Connection of Christ''s Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s role in suffering and sacrifice. Matthew highlights His purpose to give His life as a ransom, while 1 Peter describes His suffering for the unjust to bring them to God.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 28, 50, 2, 4, 8, 'to minister, and to give his life', 'Servanthood and Humility in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s servanthood and humility. Both passages emphasize that Jesus came to serve others and gave his life, demonstrating obedience and selflessness.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 28, 54, 2, 6, 6, 'to give his life a ransom for many', 'Ransom for Many and All', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of Jesus giving himself as a ransom. Matthew specifies ''ransom for many,'' while 1 Timothy expands this to ''ransom for all.'' This connection highlights the universal scope of Christ''s sacrificial role.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 28, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'to minister, and to give his life', 'Service and Sacrifice of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Christ''s selflessness. Matthew highlights Jesus'' role as a minister and his sacrificial death, while 2 Corinthians speaks to his choice to become poor for the benefit of others.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 29, 41, 10, 46, 52, 'a great multitude followed him', 'Connection of Healing and Following', 'Both passages emphasize a multitude following Jesus as he departs Jericho, highlighting the significance of his miracles. The healing of blind Bartimeus in Mark occurs as Jesus is leaving Jericho, illustrating the impact of his ministry on the crowd.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 29, 42, 18, 35, 43, 'a great multitude followed him', 'Jesus'' Journey Near Jericho', 'Both passages describe Jesus'' approach to Jericho, emphasizing the presence of a multitude. The blind man''s encounter with Jesus occurs as the crowd follows him, highlighting the significance of faith amidst the throng.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 29, 40, 9, 27, 31, 'a great multitude followed him', 'Following Jesus and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of following Jesus, with the multitude in Matthew 20:29 and the two blind men in Matthew 9:27. This connection highlights the theme of faith and the response to Jesus'' presence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
