(40, 20, 30, 40, 21, 9, 9, 'Son of David', 'Recognition of the Son of David', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as the ''Son of David'' in both passages. The blind men call out for mercy, acknowledging Jesus'' messianic title, which is echoed by the multitudes during His triumphal entry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
